<title>USA: RESEARCH ALERT-OpenVision rated a buy.</title>
<headline>RESEARCH ALERT-OpenVision rated a buy.</headline>
<text>
<p>-- Lehman Brothers said it resumed coverage of OpenVision Technologies Inc, giving the stock a buy rating.</p>
<p>-- Analyst Brian Skiba said the stock has top-line growth and margin expansion. He gave the stock a 12 month price target of $20, fifty times his projected 1998 earnings per share of $0.40.</p>
<p>-- In a statement, Skiba said the market for open systems management remains attractive, driven by the robust deployment of client/server applications.</p>
<p>-- Shares rose 1/4 to 12-3/4.</p>
</text>
